This is a known change. Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (API 30), and .NET 10 MAUI enables **edge-to-edge** display by default, which makes the old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` stop working.

## Fix: Listen for keyboard insets and adjust padding

**1. In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:**

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // React to keyboard (IME) inset changes
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navBar   = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // The bottom padding = keyboard height (or nav-bar height when closed)
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navBar.Bottom);

            v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**2. Make sure your `AndroidManifest.xml` activity has:**

```xml
android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize"
```

*(Yes, the manifest attribute still triggers inset recalculation even though the MAUI helper enum is gone.)*

**3. Your XAML stays normal — no special wrappers needed:**

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

### Why this works

Edge-to-edge means your app draws behind the keyboard and nav bar. The `WindowInsetsCompat` callback fires whenever the keyboard opens/closes, giving you the exact pixel height. Setting bottom padding on the `DecorView` pushes your entire MAUI layout above the keyboard.

### iOS

No change needed — iOS `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` in MAUI handles this automatically. If you ever need to disable it for a specific page:

```csharp
KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();
```
